<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4779889>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 2. Dorsal view of male mesosoma, with pubescence removed from left side. (a) Xylocopa bimaculata Friese, 1903, specimen from Curitiba, Paraná; (b) Xylocopa piligera Maidl, 1912, specimen from Campos do Jordão, São Paulo." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4779889/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4779893>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 3. Dorsal view of the female metasoma, with apex of metasoma shown to the left (a, c e) and detail of the terga 1–3 to the right (b, d, f) (midline of sclerite to the right in b, d, f). (a, b) Xylocopa bimaculata Friese, 1903, holotype; (c, d) Xylocopa fortuita sp. nov., holotype (shorter lateral pubescence compared to that of other two specimens is an artefact due to the condition in which the specimen was obtained; see text for details); (e, f) Xylocopa piligera Maidl, 1912, specimen from Serra da Bocaina, São José do Barreiro, São Paulo." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4779893/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4779887>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 1. Xylocopa bimaculata Friese, 1903, holotype female. (a) Head and mesosoma, dorsal view; (b) head, frontal view; (c) metasoma, dorsal view; (d) specimen labels." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4779887/files/figure.png" .

